node.title: Livestream: Defence Force gives update on NZ's response to Tonga's volcano eruption and tsunami
node.description: Aircrafts carrying much-needed supplies are due to arrive on Thursday.
node.content: ["The New Zealand Defence Force is holding a press conference about its operation response to Tonga's volcano eruption and tsunami.", "Commander of Joint Forces New Zealand, Rear Admiral Jim Gilmour, will answer questions.", "It comes as aircrafts carrying much-needed humanitarian supplies are due to arrive on Thursday, with both New Zealand and Australia sending items to the tsunami-hit country.", "Phone links between Tonga and the rest of the world began to be reconnected on Wednesday, but full internet connectivity is likely to take at least a month.", "The livestream is due to begin at 4:30pm.", "Watch it above or click here if you're using the app."]
